This article is a presidential memorandum issued by Barack Obama on March 30, 2012. The memorandum is titled "Presidential Determination Pursuant to Section 1245(d)(4)(B) and (C) of the National Defense Authorization Act for Fiscal Year 2012." 

In the memorandum, Obama states that after considering various factors such as global economic conditions, increased production by certain countries, spare capacity, and strategic reserves, he has determined that there is enough petroleum and petroleum products from countries other than Iran to allow for a significant reduction in purchases from Iran. He also mentions that he will closely monitor the situation to ensure the market can accommodate this reduction. 

The memorandum concludes by authorizing and directing the Secretary of State to publish the memorandum in the Federal Register.